#X text 34 71 For musical purposes \, you might want to set your LFOs \, triggers \, gates and whatnot according to a BPM value. The [bpm2hz] object from ELSE converts BPM to hz so and is a nice tool for this., f 50;
#X text 34 136 It also lets you set a beat length. By default it considers that the BPM corresponds to "1/4" (a quarter note) \, but you can set other relative values. For instance \, 1/8 means the time it takes for an eigth note with a 60 BPM., f 50;
